author: John Kennedy
title: Former Lt. Gov. Jennifer Carroll agrees to pay fine
text:
Former Lt. Gov. Jennifer Carroll agreed to pay a $1,000 fine Friday after acknowledging that she failed to accurately report income she received from the Internet cafe industry shortly before joining Gov. Rick Scott’s administration.
Carroll and the Florida Commission on Ethics agreed to settle the case, which stemmed from her 2013 ouster from the lieutenant governor’s post amid a criminal probe of gambling operations run by Internet cafes.
